[gd_scene load_steps=22 format=3 uid="uid://bcuttle02"]

; Cuttlefish — proper anatomy this time. Real cuttlefish have:
;  - a flattened oval mantle (wider than tall, long nose-to-tail)
;  - a continuous fringe-fin running the full length of BOTH flanks
;    (not two vertical wings like before — a horizontal ruffle)
;  - side-mounted eyes with iconic W-shaped pupils
;  - 8 short arms + 2 longer feeding tentacles below the mouth
;  - iridescent chromatophore stripes along the body
; Origin is at body center. Faces +Z (enemy.gd rotates 180° to put
; the head at Godot -Z).

